  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 2000–5500 RPM, hematocrit 35–45 %, fluid temperature 36–38 °C, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg) and validation experiments cover all boundary points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. Decision: Accepted.",
